FBIS4-49921 "drchi092_k_94006" FBIS-CHI-94-092 Daily Report 12 May 1994 NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political & Social NPC Standing Committee Removes 3 Government Ministers NPC Standing Committee Removes 3 Government Ministers OW1205051294 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0440 GMT 12 May 94 OW1205051294 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service Chinese BFN [Text] Beijing, 12 May (XINHUA) -- Decree No. 27 of the PRC President: According to a decision of the seventh meeting of the Eighth National People's Congress Standing Committee of the PRC on 12 May 1994: 1. Zhu Xun has been relieved of his duties as minister of geology and mineral resources, and Song Ruixiang has been appointed to the post. 2. Ai Zhisheng has been relieved of his duties as minister of radio, cinema, and television, and Sun Jiazheng has been appointed to the post. 3. Lu Peijian has been relieved of his duties as auditor general of the Auditing Administration, and Gu Zhenqian has been appointed to the post. [Signed] Jiang Zemin, president of the PRC [Dated] 12 May 1994
